    "attributes": {
        "action": "Establish a phone alert system for national emergencies/announcements.",
        "additional_details": "Had this system been in place at the start of this crisis, people across the country could have received announcements directly to mobile phones/devices across, instead of having to wait for announcements on TV. The Netherlands used their own system to do exactly this, and passed information regarding social distancing.",
        "background": "The Government should design and create a phone alerting system for national emergencies and announcements. During COVID-19 this could have helped create clarity and improve the speed of disseminating information. The Government looked into this in 2012 and decided not to implement it due to costs.",
